history.content: 160 isn't exactly a popular class, so you should be fine even in spite of the class size. 164 should be ok as well, though it wasn't offered in the fall so it might be slightly more crowded than usual.

Hi, I know this gets asked pretty frequently, but which CS classes would I be likely to get into if I am a Senior non-CS major and I have to phase 2 waitlist myself for a CS class? 

I want to take either 164 or 160 but those class sizes seem very small so how likely would it be for me to get into either of those? 

Also, I've already taken 188 and 186. 

Thanks!
